  ✒ Description:
      The round-mask variant of the adaptive icon, used by launchers that request a circular icon. Same two layers as ic_launcher.xml.

  ✒ Key Features:
      - Background layer bound to @color/ic_launcher_background (navy).
      - Foreground layer bound to @mipmap/ic_launcher_foreground (the custom vault mark).
      - Referenced from the manifest as android:roundIcon so circular-icon launchers pick it up automatically.

  ✒ Other Important Information:
      XML forbids double-hyphen sequences inside comments and AAPT2 hard-fails on them, so this header closes with a box-drawing rule instead of the Kotlin nine-hyphen rule. Keep this file in lockstep with ic_launcher.xml; divergence shows up as two different-looking icons across launchers.
  ─────────
